🕹️ Admin Manual: Mastering the Quiz Master Pro

Welcome, Professor. This guide takes you from the moment you wake up the server
to the moment you close a high-stakes exam.

Phase 1: Entering the Cockpit

Before you can send questions, you must "attach" your terminal to the running
bot.

1.  Start the Engine: Ensure the containers are running.
    docker-compose up -d
2.  Enter the Dashboard: Run this command to see the menu.
    docker attach quiz_bot
    💡 Pro-Tip: If the screen is blank when you enter, press Enter or type c and
    press Enter to refresh the UI.

Phase 2: Sending Quizzes (The Workflow)

You have two main weapons: Native Polls (Simple) and Premium UI (Visual/Math).

1.  Choose your UI:
      - Type 1 for a standard Telegram Poll.
      - Type 2 for the Premium UI (Best for TikZ Graphs & LaTeX).
2.  Select Subject: Type the subject number (e.g., 1) and press Enter.
3.  Choose the Range:
      - Single: 1
      - Range: 1-10
      - Mixed: 1, 3-5, 12
4.  Watch the Magic: The bot renders the images and posts them. Each message
    gets a REF ID (e.g., REF: 101) for future management.

Phase 3: The "Management" Control Room

Type 3 from the main menu to enter the Management Console.

  - n / p: Move to Next or Previous page.
  - sw (Switch): Toggle between Active quizzes and Closed quizzes.
  - ft (Filter): Type nap (Native), prp (Premium), or bop (All).
  - clean: Live-sync with Telegram. It removes "ghost" items from your list if
    you deleted them manually on the channel.
  - Close/Open: Type the Index Number (e.g., 1) or the Ref ID (e.g., ref105) to
    toggle the status.
  - Bulk Close: Type all to close everything on the current page.

Phase 4: Updating the System 🛠️

You don't need to stop the bot for everything. Here is how to handle updates:

1. Adding/Editing Questions (.json files)

  - Command: None!
  - How: Just edit the files in your questions/ folder. The bot "Hot-Reloads"
    the database every time you enter the "Send" menu. Your changes are live
    instantly.

2. Updating Logic or Features (bot.py)

  - Command: docker-compose up -d --build bot
  - How: If you change the code or requirements.txt, run this command. It
    rebuilds the bot container in seconds without touching the rendering engine.

3. Changing API Keys or Channel (config.json)

  - Command: docker-compose restart bot
  - How: Edit the file, then run this command to let the bot read the new
    settings.

Phase 5: Exiting Safely

⚠️ WARNING: Do not press Ctrl + C to leave the dashboard. This will kill the bot
process.

  - To go back in menus: Type b.
  - To shut down the bot entirely: Type 0 from the main menu.
  - To leave the dashboard but keep the bot running: Press Ctrl + P then Ctrl +
    Q. This "detaches" you safely while the bot continues to work.

🎨 Admin Cheat Sheet

| Command         | Action                       | Where to use it   |
| :-------------- | :--------------------------- | :---------------- |
| `c`             | Clear/Refresh messy screen   | Anywhere          |
| `1, 4-6`        | Send a block of questions    | Selection Screen  |
| `sw`            | See what's already ended     | Management Screen |
| `clean`         | Fix "Ghost" messages         | Management Screen |
| `all`           | End the session for students | Management Screen |
| `up -d --build` | Apply code updates           | Your Terminal     |

Now you are ready to manage your channel like a Master. 🎓
